<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-218-334  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 218 334.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Computing Canada  April 13 1989 v15 n8 p44(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>&quot;Smart&quot; building in Ontario has profitable first year. (the SussexCentre in Mississauga, Ontario)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Powell, Doug.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>The first company to claim a profit after more than a year ofoperating a 'smart' commercial building is located is Toronto,Canada.andP;  The building, the Sussex Centre in Mississauga, isdescribed by the company, Granville Technologies Inc, hascontaining its own 'mini-telephone company.' A TelecommunicationsEnhancement Link has been installed in the building to providetenants with telecommunications features such as data transmissionand receiving, video conferencing, local and wide area networking,facsimile service and a telephone system.andP;  The building uses fiberoptic technology to provide transparent transmission systems.andP;  AGranville official says that other smart buildings have provedunprofitable to manage because the task of running and maintainingthe building was left to the untrained building owners.andP;  Theofficial adds that the Sussex Centre was profitable within sixmonths of startup.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   Granville Technologies Inc. (management).andO;Topic:     Intelligent BuildingsOntarioBuilding ManagementProfitCommunications Technology.andO;Feature:   illustrationphotograph.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>